<task id="074" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6">
  <metadata>
    <title>D-C-29 + D-C-30 — Per-turn agent prompt builder gathers visible state from Assistant-visible tabs + privacy default verified</title>
    <status>completed</status>
    <estimated-effort>1 day</estimated-effort>
    <phase>Phase C — Widget Visibility Contract (Pillar 9)</phase>
    <wave>C-G2 (sequential after 073)</wave>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <dependencies>053 (workspace state wired into factory), 073 (per-widget impls)</dependencies>
    <tags>bff-api, ai, chat, workspace</tags>
    <rigor-level>FULL</rigor-level>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Modifies chat agent factory hot path; consumes workspace state + each tab's getVisibleState; privacy filter + ADR-015 binding.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>C-G2</parallel-group>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Refine the workspace state block in `SprkChatAgentFactory.CreateAgentAsync` (added in
    task 053 with a minimal text summary) to gather rich visible state from each
    Assistant-visible tab. For each tab where `visibleToAssistant: true`, call its
    registered `getAgentVisibleState()` (when defined) + include the structured output in
    the "Workspace State" prompt block. Filter logic: `tab.visibleToAssistant === true`
    AND `widget.getVisibleState` is defined. Tabs that should NOT expose to LLM
    (default state OR widget opt-out) MUST NOT appear in agent prompts (FR-59 privacy
    default).

    The frontend per-tab `getAgentVisibleState` runs in browser; BFF reaches it via the
    workspace state already persisted (the frontend pushed serialized visible state to
    BFF on tab create/update — added as part of the workspace state model). BFF
    composition reads the persisted serialized state, applies the `visibleToAssistant`
    filter, formats for prompt inclusion.

    Per spec FR-58: included in system prompt "Workspace State" block; respects
    `visibleToAssistant: true` filter per ADR-015 data governance. Per FR-59 privacy
    default: widgets that don't return state (no impl) OR tabs not flagged visible DO
    NOT appear.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior AI platform engineer + BFF engineer with familiarity with `SprkChatAgentFactory`
    + workspace state model + per-widget visibility contract.
  </role>

  <goal>
    Per-turn agent prompt builder refined; tabs with `visibleToAssistant: true` + defined
    `getVisibleState` appear in prompt; others filtered out; integration test verifies
    privacy default.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="project-spec">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/spec.md</file>
